<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870714-0027 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief:Adams-Russell Co.</HL><DD> 07/14/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> AARTENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM) </IN><TEXT>   Adams-Russell Co. said it completed its previously announced acquisition of cable-television systems in New York state from Sammons Communications Inc. for about $9.3 million and the assumption of certain debt. The cable systems operate in Wellsville, Amity, Andover, Scio, Willing, Belmont, Milo, Jerusalem, Benton and Penn Yan and serve about 7,000 customers. Adams-Russell, a Waltham, Mass., owner and operator of cable-TV systems in the Northeast, said the acquisition was financed through the company's line of credit. Sammons, based in Dallas, is a closely held operator of cable-TV systems. </TEXT></DOC>